content.description: Start on a left hand crimp and a slightly higher moon shaped ledge.  Work left to some flat ledges eventually entering into a jug rail cruising into the topout.
content.location: Found on the right side of the rock face about 10’ left of the tree you will see something crimps to the right of a higher traversing rail.

content.description: Begin sitting with staring hands in the verticals crack under the ledge.  Make easy moves up to the ledge, next bringing your heel up to lay back into a sidepull crimp and work your way out left into some smaller crimps.  Topout just above the two higher crimps.
content.location: Located on the leftmost side of Warmup 2.0 starting directly under the ledge for the topout of Low Road.

content.description: Start on the ledge under the bulge. Make your way up to a sloping crimp ledge to adjust your footing and fire up to another smaller crimp on your right. Work your way from there up to the obvious flat platform above and top out.
content.location: Located on the far right side of Warmup 2.0 where there is a slight bulge overhang next to a tree.  You will see a clear open ledge under the overhang.

content.description: Start on the right end of the clear traverse in the middle of the face, same as High Road, and traverse left on the lower rail straight through to the ledge.  Roll over on top of the ledge to topout or continue up the rock more if you feel spicy.
content.location: Located in the middle of the rock face with a clear traverse working right to left.

content.description: Start on the right end of the clear traverse in the middle of the face and traverse left staying on the higher rail.  Keep left until you reach the massive ledge to an easy topout.
content.location: Located in the middle of the rock face with a clear traverse working right to left.

content.description: Start in the middle of the crack for Low Road and make a big move to the High Road crack topping out straight up.
content.location: Located in the middle of the rock face on the jug portion of the lower crack.

pathTokens: Warm Up Area aka The Tomato Overhangs / Mack'sTraverse

content.description: A section of the Warm Up Region that clearly has been climbed but surprisingly yet to be posted.  An approximately 30’ face including primarily traverses and low/mid range problems on either end perfect to warm up on before dispersing out into The Woods.
